body:
Oh winter child&nbsp; 
Heed my call&nbsp; 
For I've read the story Of a lost soul who's been aware of awareness&nbsp; 
On the records of light and darkness
Let the loose ends be tied ends&nbsp; 
So no one pretends to regret the end of this song&nbsp; 
Let the end conceal the truth revealed to you&nbsp; 
So no one else follows the hallowed path&nbsp; 
You chose to unravel and unbind&nbsp; 
From the parallel universe above you and below us&nbsp; 
Surpass that mediocre condition of yours and join us above
On the realm where all voices, real or not, become one&nbsp; 
On the ethernal void of silence and peace&nbsp; 
Oh lone winter child Heed my call&nbsp; 
Let the razor blade be warm and soft&nbsp; 
Let the last night of the last winter&nbsp; 
Be cloudless and rainless
